<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words Ending in -ABLE — CAPABLE, DURABLE, NOTABLE" description="Top -ABLE suffix Scrabble words: CAPABLE (13pts), DURABLE (10pts), NOTABLE (9pts). Master adjective suffix bingos with the -ABLE pattern. Try it free." keywords="scrabble words ending in able, capable scrabble, durable scrabble, notable scrabble, able suffix bingo, scrabble adjective suffix">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words Ending in -ABLE — CAPABLE, DURABLE, NOTABLE","description":"Master -ABLE suffix words in Scrabble: CAPABLE (13pts), DURABLE (10pts), NOTABLE (9pts) for adjective bingos.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-able"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the best -ABLE words for Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"CAPABLE (13pts, 7 letters) leads with the C worth 3 and P worth 3. DURABLE (10pts) and NOTABLE (9pts) are also bingo-eligible. For 8-letter bingos, PASSABLE (12pts) and WORKABLE (17pts) score even higher."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why is -ABLE a powerful bingo suffix?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"-ABLE is 4 tiles (A+B+L+E) that attach to hundreds of roots. B is worth 3 points, adding base value. The suffix turns verbs into adjectives (ENJOY→ENJOYABLE) and creates natural 7-8 letter words perfect for bingo plays."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What roots combine with -ABLE for bingos?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Common 3-letter roots for 7-letter bingos: CAP(ABLE), DUR(ABLE), NOT(ABLE), SIZ(ABLE), LIV(ABLE). For 4-letter roots giving 8-letter bingos: WORK(ABLE), PASS(ABLE), SUIT(ABLE), READ(ABLE), BEAR(ABLE)."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Strategy</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in -ABLE — Adjective Suffix Bingos</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">-ABLE is the adjective-maker suffix that turns any verb into a bingo opportunity. With A, B, L, E on your rack, you only need 3 more tiles for a 7-letter play. CAPABLE leads at 13 points, DURABLE brings 10, and NOTABLE scores 9 — each earning the 50-point bonus. The B alone is worth 3 points, giving -ABLE words a scoring edge over lighter suffixes like -ING.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top Score (CAPABLE)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Suffix Tiles (ABLE)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">B Tile Value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">200+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid -ABLE Words</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top -ABLE Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 CAPABLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 points · 7 letters · C(3)+A(1)+P(3)+A(1)+B(3)+L(1)+E(1) · Double 3pt tiles</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 DURABLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 points · 7 letters · D(2)+U(1)+R(1)+A(1)+B(3)+L(1)+E(1) · Bingo eligible</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ NOTABLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 points · 7 letters · N(1)+O(1)+T(1)+A(1)+B(3)+L(1)+E(1) · All common tiles</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ SIZABLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">18 points · 7 letters · S(1)+I(1)+Z(10)+A(1)+B(3)+L(1)+E(1) · Z adds 10pts</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">-ABLE Bingo Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Recognise the stem:</span> A+B+L+E on your rack = instant bingo potential. Only 3 more tiles needed. Common roots: CAP, DUR, NOT, SIZ, LIV, PAL. Memorise 10 roots and you'll always have options.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">B adds base value:</span> Unlike -ING (all 1-point tiles), -ABLE includes B (3pts). This means your suffix alone contributes 6 points before the root even starts. -ABLE bingos average higher base scores.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Extend with UN-:</span> Many -ABLE words accept UN- prefix: UNABLE, UNCAPABLE. If the board is open, an 8-9 letter UN___ABLE play earns the bingo bonus with even more base points.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CAPABLE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DURABLE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NOTABLE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SIZABLE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">-ABLE attaches to <span class="text-white font-medium">more roots than almost any other suffix</span>. If you can think of a verb, chances are it has an -ABLE form. This makes it one of the most versatile bingo stems — memorise 10 short roots and you'll always find a play.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
